  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chief Operating Officer (Production, Operation & Warehouse)",
  "description": "<h3>Key Job Scopes</h3><ul><li><p>Provide strategic leadership and overall management of operations, production, and warehousing to ensure efficient, safe, and cost-effective manufacturing.</p></li><li><p>Plan and oversee production schedules, capacity utilisation, and workflows to meet industrial and marine customer requirements.</p></li><li><p>Manage warehouse operations including inventory control, material handling, storage, and timely dispatch.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore regulatory requirements, including MOM Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) standards and relevant industry certifications.</p></li><li><p>Drive continuous improvement initiatives to enhance productivity, quality, and operational efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Monitor operational KPIs, budgets, and performance, and report to senior management.</p></li><li><p>Adopt a hands-on leadership approach and be prepared to provide on-call operational support on a 24/7 basis.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Bachelor's Degree preferably in Mechanical orChemical Engineering</li><li>Minimum 5 years’ experience in the Manufacturing &Marine industry</li><li>Preferably with related experience in Maintenance, Repair & Overhaul (MRO) products</li><li>Preferably with related experience in Marine Medical Store requirements and regulations</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Able to handle stress and meet tight deadlines</li><li>Singaporeans & Spore PRs only</li></ul></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
